DOCUMENT();        # This should be the first executable line in the problem.

loadMacros(
"PG.pl",
"PGbasicmacros.pl",
"PGchoicemacros.pl",
"PGanswermacros.pl",
"PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl",
"PGasu.pl",
"extraAnswerEvaluators.pl"
);

TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a =  random(1,10,1);
$b =  random(1,10,1);
$c =  random(1,10,1);

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));

Solve the following inequality. Write the answer in interval notation. If the answer
involves more than one interval, write the intervals separated by the "union" symbol, U.
If needed enter \( -\infty \) as - infinity and \( \infty \) as infinity.
\[ 4|x+$a| -$b < $c \]
$BR
Answer:  \{ans_rule(40)\}
$BR
EOT

$ans1 = -($b+$c)/4-$a;
$ans2 =  ($b+$c)/4-$a;
ANS(interval_cmp("($ans1,$ans2)"));

ENDDOCUMENT();        # This should be the last executable line in the problem.
